Articles.Content:
Scott Manley built a very simple claw (for an SSTO launch) on his career play through. I've used for numerous rescue/recover options - It's a claw, medium rcs tank and 4 rcs ports, probe core, 2 parachutes, and 4 solar panels and docking port (see here

<iframe width="480" height="270" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/3durotud4Z4?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="true"></iframe>
). It can easily launch via rocket instead, use a stack separator (instead of the docking port) & fairing around it and send it up. It's got loads of rcs for minor orbital changes, docking and return. Unless you come in very aggressively you can get away without heat shields.
